Moore’s law describes the regularity that the number of transistors on integrated circuit doubles every two years. This advancement is important for other aspects of technological process in computing such as processing speed on the price of computers.
CPU clock ticks clock every times flash on and off. It means it performs operation. CPU speed measured number of on and off times per second.
If CPU speed measured in gigahertz it flashes 1 billion times. Clock is a special wire that turns on and off to keep everything synchronized. When measuring CPU performance it is essential to consider not only the clock speed but also the number of cores architecture cache size and how efficient the CPU executes and instructions
